    "description": "This is a package and a shell script for alternative polyadenylation (APA) analysis of 3' tag single-cell RNA-seq data. The shell script \"scAPAscript.R\" takes as input BAM files generated by 10x 3' tag RNA seq pipline and the results of cell clustering.\n\nAlternative polyadenylation (APA) has been indicated to play an important role in regulating mRNA stability, translation and localization.\n\nFasta and chromosome length files for human (hg19) or (and) mouse (mm10).",
